column1: As #coronavirus brings stress and uncertainty it's nice to have something to cheer for. Congratulations to #OH15 native @Joe_Burrow10. Welcome back to #Ohio! #WhoDey

Attention Self-Employed workers.  The CARES Act for COVID19 Response allows you to apply for unemployment. Hopefully the Ohio site will take applications soon. The US Department of Labor sent guidance to the states… https://t.co/ecymsZCAbW
If you are a small business affected by COVID19 please join me for a call this Friday at 2:30pm.   RSVP Now!  RSVP: https://t.co/T4vu9aN8M8  Call in: 866-757-0547 https://t.co/3SNnnQXxsY

UPDATE ➡️ in response to #COVID19 Ohio’s primary has been delayed until June 2nd. That means the polls will NOT be open today and if you would like to vote by mail you can still request an absentee ballot. For more details go to https://t.co/qImexWFmlE.
